  "original_title": "\u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3 \u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf \u0db6\u0dd0\u0db3\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca\u0d9a\u0dbb \u0dc4\u0dd2\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0dd4 \u0d87\u0db8\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dda\u0daf\u0dd3 \u0db1\u0da9\u0dd4 \u0db4\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dbd\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A Sri Lankan bond holder has filed a lawsuit in America",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A Sri Lankan bondholder has filed a lawsuit in the United States demanding payment of his money plus interest after Sri Lanka defaulted on its debt for the first time in its history, struggling to stave off economic collapse.",
        "Hamilton Reserve Bank Ltd., which owns more than $250 million in Sri Lanka's 5.875% international sovereign bonds due July 25, filed a lawsuit Tuesday in New York federal court demanding full payment of principal and interest, Bloomberg reports.",
        "Sri Lanka defaulted in May after a 30-day grace period expired for missed interest payments on two of its sovereign bonds. It was Sri Lanka's first sovereign debt default since independence from Britain in 1948.",
        "Hamilton Reserve Bank Ltd claimed in the suit that the default was orchestrated by the ruling Rajapakse family and the highest level of government officials. It also accused Sri Lanka of disposing of bonds held by domestic banks and other interested parties in an announced debt restructuring."
      ],
